    en: "The Town of Brighton does not issue its own electrician license. Instead, Chapter 62 of the Town Code requires a written application before any electrical install, alteration, or repair and directs that the work be inspected by one of three town-approved electrical inspection agencies. After the agency approves the work, the town Commissioner of Public Works issues a Certificate of Compliance. No power can be turned on until the temporary certificate or occupancy permit is issued. The Building and Planning Department at (585) 784-5250 confirms scope and answers homeowner-self-work questions before the application goes in."
